Black Pepper Sage Gravy

Ingredients
• Reserved sausage fat (approximately 30 mL / 2 tbsp)
• 30 g unsalted butter (2 tbsp)
• 30 g all-purpose flour (¼ cup minus 1 tbsp)
• 360 mL whole milk, warmed (1½ cups)
• 240 mL light chicken stock, warmed (1 cup)
• 2 g freshly ground black pepper (¾ tsp)
• 0.5 g white pepper (pinch)
• 1 g kosher salt (¼ tsp), adjust to taste
• 2–3 drops sherry vinegar or cider vinegar

Method
	1.	In the same pan, reduce heat to medium-low. Add butter to sausage fat.
	2.	Sprinkle in flour. Cook roux, stirring constantly, 2–3 minutes. Colour must remain pale blond; no browning.
	3.	Whisk in warm milk gradually until smooth.
	4.	Add stock in a thin stream, whisking continuously.
	5.	Simmer gently 6–8 minutes until nappe consistency (coats the back of a spoon).
	6.	Season with peppers and salt.
	7.	Finish with vinegar for acidity and clarity. Adjust texture with warm milk if needed.